      <li>G. Onida, L. Reining, and A. Rubio, <a class="ink-link" href="https://doi.org/10.1103/RevModPhys.74.601">"Electronic excitations: density-functional versus many-body Green's-function approaches,"</a> <em>Rev. Mod. Phys.</em> 74, 601 (2002). <span class="src-note">— GW and the Bethe–Salpeter equation, and why spectral ground truth costs what it costs.</span></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Primer>

